    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-01-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 181.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Baron Gerolt</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Fish</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of North Germany,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-01-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 14, 1871</date>. (Received January
                        14.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor of inclosing the translation of
                    a telegram, received at a late hour last night, from Count Bismarck.</p>
                <p>With the assurances of my highest consideration, I remain your most obedient
                    servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FR. v. GEROLT.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton Fish</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of
                            State, &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>[Translation.]</head>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">To the Northern German Legation</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                            >Washington</hi>, <hi rend="italic">D. C.:</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>The treatment of German merchant ships by France obliges us to revoke the
                        declaration made by us at the beginning of the war, “exempting all French
                        merchant vessels, not carrying contraband of war articles, from capture by
                        our war-vessels.”</p>
                    <p>As neutral property may have been shipped on board of French vessels in
                        confidence of the above declaration, the new measure will not be carrried
                        into effect until four weeks after this date.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>BISMARCK.</signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Versailles</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-01-13">
                                <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 13.</date>
                        </p>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
